            "content": "Hi,\\nI am having a slight confusion in the sample solutions I am seeing. When the customer gives me 20, I have two options:\\n1. To give 3 5\\'s in return\\n2. To give one 5 and one 10.\\nSuppose, I have both the options with me. Then, wouldn\\'t it be possible that the option I choose now decides my future. In other words, If I now decide to choose option 1 and fail to provide change to all customers and later realize that if I had chosen option 2 in this step, I would have been able to give change all the future customers.\\n\\nHence, I belive, this should be a recursive solution rather than deciding beforehand what option to choose\\n\\nPlease correct me If I am wrong.",
